org.h2.jaqu.annotation
Annotation Type Many2Many

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface Many2Many

Use to set a field for a many to many relationship.

Notes:

  1. Relation and Table must have a primary key, and primary key must be defined before relationship
  2. The generic type is used to infer the other object, used to get the primary key type.
  3. Lazy loading is always used, and the relationship is always two sided. (can be seen from both objects)

Author:
Shai Bentin

Required Element Summary
 java.lang.Class<?> childPkType
          The other side of the relation primary key field should be named here.
 java.lang.Class<?> childType
          The class type of the related object.
 java.lang.String joinTableName
          The name of the DB table maintaining the relationship.
 java.lang.String relationColumnName
          The name of the column representing the other side of the relation.
 java.lang.String relationFieldName
          The name of the field in the target object holding the other side of the relationship.
 
Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.String myFieldNameInRelation
          If empty then column name will be used, otherwise denotes the name of the column representing 'this' side in the relationship table.
 

Element Detail

childType

public abstract java.lang.Class<?> childType
The class type of the related object.

joinTableName

public abstract java.lang.String joinTableName
The name of the DB table maintaining the relationship. Default no relation table

relationColumnName

public abstract java.lang.String relationColumnName
The name of the column representing the other side of the relation. Must have value!

relationFieldName

public abstract java.lang.String relationFieldName
The name of the field in the target object holding the other side of the relationship. If null 'this' tableName will be used!

childPkType

public abstract java.lang.Class<?> childPkType
The other side of the relation primary key field should be named here. Correlates to the relation table

myFieldNameInRelation

public abstract java.lang.String myFieldNameInRelation
If empty then column name will be used, otherwise denotes the name of the column representing 'this' side in the relationship table.

Default:
""
